  "text": "We explain how to calculate U RE(t, e) using Fig. 4 . Fig. 4 (a) shows an intermediate tree t (represented by thick lines). Now candidate edges that can be added to t are 2-5, 4-5, 4-7 and 6-7. Here we explain only the cases for 4-7 and 6-7. Table 2 shows entries in a given routing table which are related to these two edges. By adding 6-7 to t (Fig. 4 (b) ), < 4, 7 > is made uncoverable by condition (1) because adding 4-7 results in a closed path. Also, < 1, 7 > is made uncoverable by condition (2) because a packet arriving at node 1 is indicated to be forwarded to node 4 in the given routing table, but to be forwarded to node 3 by the algorithmic routing using this tree. Similarly, < 2, 7 >, < 7, 1 >, < 7, 2 > and < 7, 4 > are made uncoverable by condition (2). However, < 2, 7 > is not in U RE(t, 6-7) because this entry was already made uncoverable by condition (1) when edges 1-2 and 1-4 were added to the tree. Therefore, |U RE(t,6-7)| is 5. On the other hand, by adding 4-7 to t (Fig. 4 (c) ), < 6, 7 > by condition (1) and < 3, 7 >, < 7, 3 > and < 7, 6 > by condition [CITATION_1] are made uncoverable. So, |U RE(t,4-7)| is 4. Therefore, 4-7 is added to t.",
